INS PROPOSES ELECTRONIC PASSENGER TRACKING
(Source: Computerworld) 
The INS wants to electronically track U.S. and non-U.S. citizen travel into and out of the country, matching biographical data with advance arrival and departure notification.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779356

MICROSOFT LAUNCHES NEW AND IMPROVED MEDIA PLAYER
